</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33F6520EE0EFFCEFF63FD7AFD2C56AF" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9A36ABEE0EFFCEFF63FD7AFF6F5790" blockId="7.[130,777,695,1008]" box="[132,197,695,721]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">NOTE</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9A36ABEE0EFFCEFF63FD1BFD2C56AF" blockId="7.[130,777,695,1008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">
This species is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0EFFCEFDA5FD1AFCA257AF" authority="Pojark." authorityName="Pojark." box="[578,776,726,753]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0EFFCEFDA5FD1AFD1957AF" box="[578,691,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. persicus</emphasis>
Pojark.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0EFFCEFF6AFD3BFEEC564F" author="RAEI NIAKI N." bookContentInfo="207 p." box="[141,326,758,784]" firstAuthor="Raei Niaki" journalOrPublisher="University of Tehran, Tehran" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" refId="ref5383" refString="RAEI NIAKI N. 2019. - Biosystemtic Studies on the Genus Cotoneaster Medik. (Rosaceae) in Iran with Emphasis on the Micromorphological, Biochemical and Molecular Data. PhD thesis, University of Tehran, Tehran, 207 p." title="Biosystemtic Studies on the Genus Cotoneaster Medik. (Rosaceae) in Iran with Emphasis on the Micromorphological, Biochemical and Molecular Data" type="book" year="2019">Raei Niaki 2019</bibRefCitation>
) The latter is widely distributed in Fars, Isfahan, and Kerman provinces (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0EFFCEFE08FCDBFD0D566F" author="KHATAMSAZ M." box="[495,679,790,816]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" pagination="209 - 239" refId="ref4690" refString="KHATAMSAZ M. 1992. - Cotoneaster Medik., in ASSADI M. (ed.), Flora of Iran. Research institute of forests and rangelands publication, Tehran 6: 209 - 239 [in Persian]." type="journal article" year="1992">Khatamsaz 1992</bibRefCitation>
). Leaves of both species are small and ovate with red fruits. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0EFFCEFF63FC9BFEA5562F" box="[132,271,854,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="afghanicus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0EFFCEFF63FC9BFEA5562F" box="[132,271,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. afghanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0EFFCEFE71FC9BFDAE562F" box="[406,516,854,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="persicus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0EFFCEFE71FC9BFDAE562F" box="[406,516,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">C. persicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its obtuse to rounded apex of leaves (vs acute), base of leaves rounded to obtuse (vs cuneate to narrowly cuneate), and 1-4 flowers per inflorescence (vs 5-8 flowers) (
<figureCitation id="131E2A2EEE0EFFCEFEDEFC7BFE03568F" box="[313,425,950,976]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="8.[132,143,1986,2003]" captionTargetBox="[199,1388,215,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-29@8.[198,1389,214,1802]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIG. 4. — Cotoneaster afghanicus G.Klotz leaves and fruits outline (A) and close up (B). Collection number: Faghihnia &amp; Zangooei 27111 (FUMH); determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573119" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573119/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Fig. 4A, B</figureCitation>
). This species occurs in 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0EFFCEFD4FFC7BFF1856AF" name="Afghanistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, Kashmir (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0EFFCEFECDFC1BFDB956AF" author="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B." box="[298,531,981,1008]" pageId="7" pageNumber="146" refId="ref4629" refString="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B. 2009. - Cotoneasters: A Comprehensive Guide to Shrubs for Flowers, Fruit, and Foliage. Timber press, Portland, London, 344 p." type="book" year="2009">Fryer &amp; Hylmö 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0EFFCEFDB5FC1BFD2856AF" box="[594,642,982,1008]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="146">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
